OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSocial care: Boris Johnson 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdefends his plan amid      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fcriticism over the cost cap
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Boris Johnson has insisted his plan for
OL,6, social care will help tackle a "long   
OL,7, standing social injustice" over cost.  
OL,9,FThe government unveiled its suite of   
OL,10,Fproposals in September, including an   
OL,11,F#86,000 cap on personal care costs.    
OL,13,FBut an amendment to the plan, published
OL,14,Flast week, said support payments from  
OL,15,Fcouncils will not count towards the    
OL,16,Fcap, with charities warning the move   
OL,17,Fwould unfairly hit the poorest.        
OL,19,FThe prime minister insisted the new    
OL,20,Fsystem would be "incredibly generous". 
